message.content:
cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the effect of ISP traffic shaping on user-perceived performances in broadband access networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category as traffic shaping can potentially impact the security and privacy of user data. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper uses streaming video traffic as one of the objective measures of user-perceived performances. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper investigates the effect of traffic shaping on multiple subscribers interacting in a shared access network. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper uses objective and quantifiable measures of user-perceived performances for different types of traffic.
